 eNCA senior reporter Siphamandla Goge is covering the conference proceedings. #DStv403 EAST LONDON - The next couple of hours are crucial for the ANC's Eastern Cape elective conference. It's the third day and proceedings are yet to commence amid court cases and interdicts. READ: ANC Eastern Cape conference enters third day Outgoing ANC Provincial chairperson in the Eastern Cape Oscar Mabuyane has welcomed the court's decision to dismiss an attempt to exclude some branches from participating in the conference. Saturday's open conference session got heated when delegates raised grievances. READ: ANC EC interdict bid struck off the roll Commissions will report back to the plenary regarding credentials. Meanwhile, ANC Convenor of Deployees to the Eastern Cape, Aaron Motsoaledi, says the list of delegates who are going to vote is being finalised. He says organisers are ensuring that everyone who comes to the conference is a registered delegate.